title: Binary Search
description: Write a Python function that implements binary search on a sorted list. If it is not in the list return -1
constraints: Constraints: The list will contain integers.
test:
def passTest():
	solution = Solution()
	param = [[[1, 3, 5, 7, 9], 5], [[10, 20, 30, 40, 50], 10], [[2, 4, 6, 8, 10], 10], [[1, 3, 5, 7, 9], 5], [[], 5]]
	ans = [2, 0, 4, -1, -1]
	for i in range(5):
		if ans[i] == solution.binarySearch(param[i]):
			continue
		else
			return False
	return True
passedTest = 'Passed all test cases' if passTest() else 'Test cases failed'
print(passedTest)
